{ Let's start with Nc3. This is called the Main Line. The White player begins to develop his pieces. The goal with Nc3 is to protect the e4 Pawn. } { [%cal Rd5e4] }
1. Nc3 { Black captures the e4 Pawn. } { [%cal Gc3e4,Rd5e4] } 1... dxe4 { White captures the Pawn with Nxe4. } 2. Nxe4 { This is the Caro-Kann Main Line. Possible continuation are:
1. Bf5, the Classical Variation;
2. Nd7, the Karpov Variation;
3. Nf6. } { [%cal Gc8f5,Gb8d7,Gg8f6] } *


