{ In this position, the best move for Black is Bf5. This is the Classic Variation. } { [%cal Gc8f5] }
1... Bf5 { The best move! It is the best because this move expels the knight from the central square e4. White plays Ng3. } { [%cal Rf5e4] } 2. Ng3 { Remove your Bishop with Bg6. } { [%cal Rg3f5] } 2... Bg6 { Now the goal for White is to castle as soon as possible, this is the reason why in the next two moves it move the Knight and Bishop on the Kingside. White plays Nf3. } 3. Nf3 { Play Nd7 to avoid the knight jump to e5. } { [%cal Gf3e5] } 3... Nd7 { White plays Bd3. } 4. Bd3 { The dark-squared Bishop is very sad. How would you bring that Bishop to life? It's your turn find the best move for Black. } 4... e6 { Well, the Bishop has life, but it needs a better square at the next move. In the meanwhile, White castle its King. } 5. O-O { Bishop needs a better square, can you find it? } 5... Bd6 { Congratulations! You completed this lesson. } *


