{ In the Exchange Variation the White player prefers to be in an open position and capture the Black Pawn with 3. exd5. }
1. exd5 { Capture the White Pawn with 3. ... cxd5. } 1... cxd5 { White plays Bd3. } 2. Bd3 { Develop your Knight that will threathen the d4 Pawn. Play Nc6. } 2... Nc6 { White protect the d4 Pawn playing c3 and creating a good Pawn structure. } 3. c3 { Develop your other Knight. } { [%cal Gb2d4] } 3... Nf6 { White play Bf4. } 4. Bf4 { It's time to develop your Bishop, what is the best development square for our Bishop? } 4... Bg4 { Very well! This is one of the ways to play for the black player, as there is a quick 4.f4 in this variation. } *


