{ It may seem a bit weird to you, but I think you already know what the first moves of caro-kann are, so I wanted to take you to what I really want to show you.

In the Exchange Variation, the white player can also play 4.c4. This is called the "Panov attack". }
1. c4 { How can you give the d5 pawn some extra support? } 1... Nf6 { Very well I see that you know the theory of the Caro-Kann Defense. } 2. Nc3 { Develop your other Knight. } 2... Nc6 { White plays Nf3. } 3. Nf3 { Play 3. g6 } 3... g6 { White capture with cxd5. } 4. cxd5 { What would you play in this position? } 4... Nxd5 { Soon you will be able to move the Bishop to g7 and finish the development. } *


